# Step 3 — Update memory so we don't repeat work

At the **end of a task** (or before closing out a multi-step change), update the project memory files under `docs/memory/` when relevant:

1. **`docs/memory/done_index.md`** — Mark today's deliverable as completed (date + short description).
2. **`docs/memory/lessons_learned.md`** — Add any new learnings from this task.
3. **`docs/memory/error_patterns.md`** — If a confusion or mistake occurred, record it here along with the fix.
4. **`docs/memory/open_questions.md`** — Add new unresolved items with concrete verification steps; remove or update when resolved.
5. **`docs/memory/backlog.md`** — Remove completed items and reprioritize the next tasks.

- Only update files that have something new to record; don't add empty or filler entries.
- Keep entries short and actionable so future sessions can reuse them without re-explaining.
